title.98: Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace Manga (1999) #2

description.2: Guest-starring the Heroes for Hire! Killmonger and Boss Morgan are determined to tear apart Harlem. Black Panther joins Iron Fist, Power Man, Misty Knight and Falcon to protect the streets. But can T'Challa stand to defeat his own brother?
description.3: Sharon Carter has gone missing and disappeared to one of the most dangerous places in the universe... The Savage Land!
description.4: While everyone's wondering what they would do if they were Spider-Girl and had super powers, Spider-Girl's out fighting those that call themselves "The Soldiers of the Serpent"!
description.5: Cyclops, the original X-Man, has fallen in battle with Apocalypse.  Now that the villain has been defeated, how do Xavier, the X-Men and Magneto move on from here?
description.7: The tyrant who twisted Logan into the Horseman of Death is no more, but his effects on Wolverine remain! With his healing factor gone, can Logan survive an internal attack?
description.8: What's a team of mutants without any mutant powers? The X-Men are about to find out...and the consequences of their de-powering are dire!
description.11: Which planet will Dr. Doom save: Earth or Planet Doom?! The generals (and their vast armies) finally make their move on Earth! Dr. Doom can control them, but which planet will he spare...the one he lives on now or the one that he could rule?
description.16: Frank Castle has gone back to basics. Back in New York, back from the dead and back doing what he does best: exterminating bad guys and waging his personal war on crime. The Punisher is here to clean up the mean streets of New York City.
description.17: Tony's life implodes as Iron Man's identity is revealed to the public. Cast out of his business and susceptible to enemies, who will Stark turn to in his hour of greatest need?
description.18: Can Moondragon help Captain Marvel master his newfound, and uncontrollable Cosmic Awareness? And where Moondragon travels, can Drax the Destroyer be far behind? Plus: More problems for Rick Jones and Marlo!
description.19: While dealing with the loss of Cyclops, Cable loses his telekinesis. But what happens when his power was the only thing holding back a demonic possession?
description.22: Ever since the defeat of the Goblin Queen, anti-mutant sentiment has grown to dangerous levels on the Mutant X world. In the midst of this boiling hatred, Havok finds himself needing to rescue an enemy when a member of an anti-mutant youth group discovers that he himself is a mutant. But Alex Summers isn't the only one who has tracked down the boy, because he's also in the crosshairs of the Punisher!
description.24: The Galaxy's greatest comics anthology features the world's greatest comics creators and their spins on the'Star Wars'saga, both within and beyond the continuity!'Lando Calrissian'gambles for an immense prize: an entire city!'Jar Jar Binks'discovers that the bonds of friendship can only be stretched so far. And an unlikely pair take'the galaxy'by storm!
description.25: As Lannik terrorists and Ffib priests prepare to wipe out half of the Jedi Council, the Jedi must ask themselves: is there any hope for peace, or was this a ruse all along? The answer lies somewhere among the rocky flats and methane pools of Malastare, but so does death, and for one of the team, life will never be the same again!
description.26: Three more stories of'Chewbacca's past unfold:'Lando Calrissian'and Chewbacca must fight for their lives in a corrupt'Imperial'arena!'Rogue Squadron'pilot'Wedge Antilles'flies off to battle with a very furry, very angry, and very unwilling passenger! And'Leia Organa Solo'grows solemn with a story of'her husband's'lifelong friend.
description.31: The demise of Demon Bear leads to the creation of four Dani Moonstars? Arcadia will destroy X-Force and do so with an army of X-dopplegangers!
description.35: Iron Man's identity is threatened following a tussle with Whiplash. Rumiko confronts her feelings for Tony.
description.36: Captain Marvel, the Hulk and Wendigo battle it out in the Canadian wildnerness. But the most deadly threat Marlo faces will be a surprise...and there is already a body count.
description.37: THE ANSWER LIES WITH DOOM! Spider-Man comes face-to-face once again with Doctor Doom during his quest to Latveria where he believes Mary-Jane is being held after her plane crash.
description.43: The Killmonger, the one villain Black Panther has never defeated, returns from the dead! First thing to do in this new life? Take down Everett Ross! Meanwhile, T'Challa is attacked in Harlem by Nightshade!
description.44: The Hatemonger has chained The Falcon and an American hero to two missiles and launched them! Can Captain America and Nick Fury stop them in time to rescue their friends?
description.45: The Daily Bugle assigns May to discover the true identity of the "sky bandit".
description.46: The X-Men are in a reailty that is not their own.  Have them found themselves in a new Age of Apocalypse?
description.49: In the Ages of Apocalypse, a new Fantastic Four has formed of Wovlerine, Hulk, Spider-Man and Ghost Rider. Can this new foursome take down the likes of Blastaar, Annihilus and Dr. Doom?
description.50: The merged being of Cyclops and Apocalypse continue to ravage time.  Will Jean be able to save Scott before Cable is forced to end his own father?
description.53: Victor Von Doom and Susan Storm Richards are getting married!? And the Human Torch (brother of the bride) and the Thing (one of her best friends) intend to stand by her side as she takes her vows?! Obviously, something is seriously out of kilter here. After all, what happened to Sue's husband, Mr. Fantastic?
description.55: The evil Spider-Woman is back with a vengeance, and she wants to take poor little Mattie down bad! It's the knock-down, drag-out slugfest you've been waiting for! Plus: What will happen between Spider-Man and Spider-Woman now that Mattie has learned Peter Parker's secret identity?! And don't miss the disgusting return of Flesh, sans Bones!
description.59: In Egypt, Cable battles the Pharaoh and his army!
description.60: As the world of Malastare begins to thrum to the rocket thrusts of the galaxy's greatest Podracers, the Jedi Council members are threatened from all sides! Lannik Terrorists, Ffib priests, and half of the galaxy's most nefarious crime lords are here, and justice is the last thing on their minds! And in the hard-bitten world of Podracing, they've never stopped a race just because a few sentients have tumbled onto the track?even if those unfortunate beings are Jedi Knights!
description.61: A humorous glance into the making of a Star Wars comic! What happens when a super-fan gets the opportunity to create a Star Wars story all his own? Disillusionment and avoidance of reality go a long way in making this fan's dream come true!
description.62: Three more stories of'Chewbacca's past unfold: an old'Trandoshan'slaver speaks of his nemesis with reverence and a hint of fear; a diminutive bounty hunter, the victim of betrayal, is saved by a massive, furred hand;'a young Imperial cadet'defies'his commander'and refuses to'torture'a Wookiee'prisoner, setting the stage for one of the greatest partnerships'the galaxy'has ever seen!
description.63: Wedding Day! But as the guests are taking their places, the Imperial's disruption of the festivities begins! Swoop riders are raiding the building and a madman with a vest-full of explosives is threatening to take the entire building down! Who can save the saviors of the galaxy?
description.69: Presumed dead after Mary-Jane's plane crashes, Peter Parker is left alone and that makes room for new women to enter his lives!
description.73: Ultimo's enhanced tech makes him a tricky foe for Iron Man...and Golden-Blade and Sapper! Warbird seeks a path of recovery.
description.74: Look out! It's an official stop on the Hulk Smash World Tour! As Captain Marvel continues to struggle with his newfound Cosmic Awareness, matters go from bad to worse when Rick Jones is once again reunited with the jade giant! And, off in space, another notable Marvel character heads for Earth in response to Genis' plight... and when they meet, the sparks really start to fly!
description.75: Psychic claws battle metal jaws when Rina, the Wild Thing takes on a robotic monster! And he ain't no gentle iron giant! Plus: J2 takes his own walk on the wild side! Crazed action? Check! Super hero silliness? Right again!
description.76: It's a father/son bonding experience, X-Men style! Cyclops and Cable take a trip through time and space!
description.77: Apocalypse has turned his attention to the cosmic characters that walk among us! His plan: Spark an all-out war between the humans and the subterranean-dwelling Deviants to learn who is worthy of survival! And only a handful of beings can save the day... all-powerful beings known as the Eternals! This wondrous one-shot uncovers several revelations about these fascinating entities' true place in the Marvel Universe and introduces new Eternals!
description.84: Spider-Man and the Hulk...fighting?! Has the Hulk's uncontrollable rage gotten the best of him yet again?
description.85: Featuring the Incredible Hulk! There stands Everett Ross, proxy King of Wakanda, under the green goliath's gaze! Plus, a Wakandan Royal Hunt goes awry when Everett bucks tradition. Black Panther deals with the backhand of bureaucracy.
description.86: The Hatemonger has returned with a vengeance and is determined to defeat Captain America and The Falcon.
description.87: In their final issue, the Fantastic Five must fight Diablo to help a friend in need.
description.88: In this alternate world Matt Murdock is dead and Kaine holds Kingpin responsible for it all. With one New York City super hero down, it's only right we bring back the original... SPECTACULAR SPIDER-MAN!
description.89: Apocalypse has assembled the Twelve and he's going to use their combined energies to make himself nigh immortal.
description.90: While Logan battles Warren, Psylocke risks freeing the Shadow King.
description.91: Cyclops makes a terrible sacrifice to save his teammates.
description.94: Only one man walked away from last issue's final battle, and his name is Dr. Doom! Mr. Fantastic and Victor von Doom confronted the Dreaming Celestial, and only the FF's arch-enemy is left standing! Worse, he commands an army that can lay waste to the entire planet! Can the remaining three members of the Fantastic Four hope to stop them, or even survive? Finally, where do Valeria von Doom's loyalties lie: with the Invisible Woman (whom she calls mother) or with her supposed father, Dr. Doom?
description.95: Half of the Jedi Council has been sent to the world of Malastare?one of the last worlds to hold Podraces?to negotiate a peace treaty between two warring factions. But the whole affair is being manipulated by a secret, third party, out to assassinate the Jedi! This story arc features many familiar characters from The Phantom Menace. Witness the ongoing adventures that bridge the gap between Episodes I & II!'
description.96: See for the first time ever, the history of'the galaxy's greatest'Wookiee! This special first issue features stories narrated by'Mallatobuck, Chewbacca's wife, and Attichitcuk, Chewbacca's father.'
description.99: As Luke and Mara gather their friends about them and prepare to share their vows, another vow is also closer to being fulfilled: Imperial Moff Takkar pledges the destruction of this wedding, a travesty and an insult to the memory of the once-great Empire!

0.text: The new Galactus has arrived...to save Earth X?

1.text: Venom and Sandman duking it out sounds like a win-win scenario for the good guys! Until things turn sour!

6.text: Spider-Man and Vulture battle in New York City to see things through! Their fight is multiple stories above street-level, where many innocent people lay below…

9.text: Meet the most dangerous new foe the Hulk has ever encountered! His name is Ryker, and he's been secretly dogging the green goliath's tracks for years! Who is he? What does he want with Bruce Banner? And just how does his shadowy, long-term agenda connect to the testing of an experimental gamma bomb all those years ago?

10.text: Hawkeye faces both a turning point and a new Thunderbolt! The only hope the Thunderbolts have of helping their former teammate Abe Jenkins is by bringing down the new Beetle and blackmailing the Commission! But will Hawkeye compromise his morals to save his friend, and will his partners discover that he lied about the Commission's pardon? Plus: A new T-Bolt is introduced!

12.text: With Gambit M.I.A., Rogue grabs the spotlight! Searching for Remy LeBeau, Rogue travels to Latveria, and instead enters the otherworldly walls of the Folding City, which also hold the Mengo Brothers! Who is Exalt, leader of the Folding City...and why do the Brothers call him "Daddy"? And just where the heck is Gambit anyway?

13.text: The entire team is stripped of their mutant abilities! ‘Nuff said!

15.text: It's Thor versus Thanos in a battle for the future!

20.text: The team finds themselves caught in the torrential storms that surround the Savage Land! And to make matters worse, their makeshift hot-air balloon is beginning to break apart! Also, you'll never believe what happens when Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters is paid a visit by Candy Southern!

21.text: Nocturne infects the Baxter Building with a bio-mechanic organism which Walkabout must rescue. Reed Richards discovers a Skrull scoutship because of a Skrull spy.

23.text: The Reaper has awakened, and is attacking Silvereye! But even the forces of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s elite vampire-hunting unit seem helpless against this undead assault! But when all seems lost, from the flames of defeat comes Blade! But with the fate of mankind in the balance, and his own vampiric urges flaring up, can he defeat the invulnerable immortal?

28.text: Captain America recruits his own team of heroes to infiltrate the Triune Understanding's New York Headquarters. But not all is what it seems. What is Cap hiding?

30.text: Who is the mysterious deaf woman with uncanny abilities? Daredevil will find out soon enough! Why is this woman gunning for DD and what does it have to do with Kingpin?

34.text: Thor makes a terrible discovery when he travels to Asgard to seek the council of the gods.

38.text: A battle between Phoenix and Ch'vayre? In a world where Apocalypse reigns, Rachel Summers and her band of misfits must destroy the overlord! But just as Rachel seeks out the mysterious Order, she is attacked by one of her own. A new dawn for humanity begins here!

39.text: Everyone wants a piece of Nick Fury, dead or alive! Deathlok is recruited by Dum Dum Dugan to locate Fury, while the Clown receives similar orders from his higher-ups. Which mercenary will reach Fury first? He who gets the spoils…decides the fate of Nick Fury!

41.text: Black Bolt has failed to prevent Earth X's destruction...or has he?  Who is the final hope for the doomed planet?

42.text: Mary Jane may be missing…but Doctor Doom has been found!

47.text: Trapped in the dreaded Negative Zone, Spider-Man fights on the side of the insurrectionists against the overwhelming power of the monstrous Blastaar! And just when it seems most bleak, the wall-crawler discovers the most unlikely ally ever in the crimson killer called Carnage!

48.text: Adrian Toomes, commonly known as the Vulture, is back and badder than ever. Spider-Man has to defeat him but there is one little caveat -- Vulture has the home-field advantage in this aerial battleground!

51.text: A new version of the Hulk is introduced here! The only hope that Bruce Banner has to halt the monstrosity ravaging his mindscape is to unite the various components of his shattered psyche! But can any threat bring together the savage Hulk, the gray model, the intelligent version and Banner himself? And before it's all over, a new Hulk, different from all others, will stand revealed!

52.text: The Thunderbolts' mission: Bring in the Beetle, even if that means taking on Justin Hammer and his horde of super-villain hirelings! But when the helmet comes off, will it be Mach-1 under the armor...or someone else? Meanwhile, the architect behind the tragedy that befell the 'Bolts in issue #34 claims a new victim, and the first major clue to his identity is dropped!

54.text: The conclusion to the Savage Land saga! Separated since their arrival in the prehistoric jungle, the X-Men reunite against their greatest foe: Magneto! Guest-starring Ka-Zar, Polaris and Havok!

55.text: The evil Spider-Woman is back with a vengeance, and she wants to take poor little Mattie down bad! It's the knock-down, drag-out slugfest you've been waiting for! Plus: What will happen between Spider-Man and Spider-Woman now that Mattie has learned Peter Parker's secret identity?! And don't miss the disgusting return of Flesh, sans Bones!

56.text: Blade finally surrenders to the undead curse he has fought for so long, and goes on a rampage inside a S.H.I.E.L.D. Silvereye airship! But all this pales besides the epic struggle that occurs when the vampire hunter goes fang-to-fang with his bestial nemesis, Hrolf!

58.text: Continuing his adventure in 1892, Gambit makes a deal with the Devil himself, Mr. Sinister! But will this diabolical pact protect the Thieves' Guild, or will it unleash the dreaded power of Apocalypse?! Plus: The New Son meets the high-flying Angel!

64.text: The Avengers interrupt Juggernaut's execution and battle the Exemplars. Plus: an Avenger takes a leave from the active roster!

68.text: Deathlok taps into his remaining humanity when he meets with his sister. Will Jack Truman ever feel the unification of body and mind again? Plus, an attack from the Serpent Society turns a happy reunion into a dangerous one!

70.text: Deep in the recesses of her mind, Danielle Moonstar battles the Demon Bear. With her burgeoning mystic abilities out-of-whack, will Dani be able to defeat the demons of her past? And will she cope with the choices she must make for her future?

71.text: Nate Grey is trapped in a nightmarish wasteland of Apocalypse’s making!

72.text: Thor's alter-ego, Jake, is under the control of a puppet master. And that puppet master is Loki!

78.text: Virtually every heavyweight hero stars in this planet-shattering conclusion! The Avengers, the Starjammers, the Imperial Guard, the Fantastic Four and the Silver Surfer make their last stand to save the Shi'ar homeworld! If they succeed in destroying Galactus, the universe will be saved...or will it?!

79.text: New York, 1891. A place of corruption. And now, a place where Gambit finds himself...side-by-side with his father! It's a race to find the man called Sinister, as the secrets of the Thieves Guild and the Clan LeBeau are revealed! Plus: Who or what is the Black Womb?

81.text: Still embroiled in the mysteries of the Savage Land, Cyclops and Beast search for Jean Grey. Meanwhile, high above them, Angel confronts revelations that may doom his teammates and himself! And coming to the rescue: Havok and Polaris!

82.text: Sinister stirrings! Guess who's back to steal Summers DNA to create his own X-Man?

83.text: Is Blade both a vampire and a member of the secret sect called Silvereye? Our hero thinks so! But does this bizarre turn of events play into the hands of the awakening fiend known as the Reaper...or is the disoriented Blade now more of a wild card than ever before? And while our deranged slayer rampages, what of the mysterious figure that stirs in the gross, green goop-filled tank?

92.text: The Hulk becomes INCREDIBLE once again! A perfect jump-on spot for readers! The life of Dr. Bruce Banner was irrevocably changed the day that he was caught in the heart of a gamma bomb explosion. For it was on that day that he was transformed into the most powerful creature to ever walk the Earth, the rampaging man-monster that mankind came to know as the incredible Hulk! And ever since that day his life has been filled with horror and hardships. But if you think every terrible thing that could be done to Banner has already happened, think again! And in the aftermath of this issue's shocking development, Banner must undertake a journey into his own psyche in an attempt to reunite the various fractured shards of his personality! And in this case, that means facing different versions of the Hulk...including new incarnations you've never seen before!

93.text: The Thunderbolts grapple with the devastating loss they suffered last issue, even as the architect of their misery targets his next victim! And the mystery of Abe Jenkins' whereabouts deepens as the armored Beetle attacks Justin Hammer's organization! Has Mach-1 reverted to his former identity, or is something even stranger afoot?

97.text: The Hulk's greatest enemy has always been his own inner demons.  Will the Hulk finally succumb to his inner darkness?
